The paper proposes a dynamic network model and applies it to the interbank market. The model involves latent variables and Markov dynamics, which are commonly used in machine learning and statistical inference, suggesting that the paper could belong to sub-categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SD (Software Engineering), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with network formation and link prediction, which are topics in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
